#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an8.64"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an8.64:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 8 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 8 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.64:0.2"
msgid "7. Bhūmicālavagga "
msgstr "7. Earthquakes "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 64. Gayāsīsasutta → adhidevañāṇadassanasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an8.64:0.3"
msgid "64. Gayāsīsasutta "
msgstr "64. At Gāyā Head "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an8.64:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā gayāyaṃ viharati gayāsīse. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Gāyā on Gāyā Head. "

msgctxt "an8.64:1.2"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi … pe … "
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.64:1.3"
msgid "“pubbāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sambodhā anabhisambuddho bodhisattova samāno obhāsaññeva kho sañjānāmi, no ca rūpāni passāmi. (1) "
msgstr "“Mendicants, before my awakening—when I was still not awake but intent on awakening—I perceived light but did not see visions. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an8.64:2.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me, "

msgctxt "an8.64:2.2"
msgid "‘sace kho ahaṃ obhāsañceva sañjāneyyaṃ rūpāni ca passeyyaṃ; "
msgstr "‘What if I were to both perceive light and see visions? "

msgctxt "an8.64:2.3"
msgid "evaṃ me idaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ parisuddhataraṃ assā’ti. "
msgstr "Then my knowledge and vision would become even more purified.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an8.64:3.1"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, aparena samayena appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto obhāsañceva sañjānāmi, rūpāni ca passāmi; "
msgstr "So after some time, living alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute, I perceived light and saw visions. "

# NOTE: Note that this passage clarifies exactly what the stock phrase rupani passami: seeing visions of the gods. Translating it as “see forms” hardly captures this.
msgctxt "an8.64:3.2"
msgid "no ca kho tāhi devatāhi saddhiṃ santiṭṭhāmi sallapāmi sākacchaṃ samāpajjāmi. (2) "
msgstr "But I didn’t associate with those deities, converse, or engage in discussion. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an8.64:4.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me, "

msgctxt "an8.64:4.2"
msgid "‘sace kho ahaṃ obhāsañceva sañjāneyyaṃ, rūpāni ca passeyyaṃ, tāhi ca devatāhi saddhiṃ santiṭṭheyyaṃ sallapeyyaṃ sākacchaṃ samāpajjeyyaṃ; "
msgstr "‘What if I were to perceive light and see visions; and associate with those deities, converse, and engage in discussion? "

msgctxt "an8.64:4.3"
msgid "evaṃ me idaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ parisuddhataraṃ assā’ti. "
msgstr "Then my knowledge and vision would become even more purified.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an8.64:5.1"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, aparena samayena appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto obhāsañceva sañjānāmi, rūpāni ca passāmi, tāhi ca devatāhi saddhiṃ santiṭṭhāmi sallapāmi sākacchaṃ samāpajjāmi; "
msgstr "So after some time … I perceived light and saw visions. And I associated with those deities, conversed, and engaged in discussion. "

msgctxt "an8.64:5.2"
msgid "no ca kho tā devatā jānāmi—"
msgstr "But I didn’t know which "

msgctxt "an8.64:5.3"
msgid "imā devatā amukamhā vā amukamhā vā devanikāyāti. (3) "
msgstr "orders of gods those deities came from. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.303, sc6
msgctxt "an8.64:6.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me, "

msgctxt "an8.64:6.2"
msgid "‘sace kho ahaṃ obhāsañceva sañjāneyyaṃ, rūpāni ca passeyyaṃ, tāhi ca devatāhi saddhiṃ santiṭṭheyyaṃ sallapeyyaṃ sākacchaṃ samāpajjeyyaṃ, tā ca devatā jāneyyaṃ: "
msgstr "‘What if I were to perceive light and see visions; and associate with those deities, converse, and engage in discussion; "

msgctxt "an8.64:6.3"
msgid "“imā devatā amukamhā vā amukamhā vā devanikāyā”ti; "
msgstr "and find out which orders of gods those deities come from? "

msgctxt "an8.64:6.4"
msgid "evaṃ me idaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ parisuddhataraṃ assā’ti. "
msgstr "Then my knowledge and vision would become even more purified.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an8.64:7.1"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, aparena samayena appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto obhāsañceva sañjānāmi, rūpāni ca passāmi, tāhi ca devatāhi saddhiṃ santiṭṭhāmi sallapāmi sākacchaṃ samāpajjāmi, tā ca devatā jānāmi: "
msgstr "So after some time … I perceived light and saw visions. And I associated with those deities … And I found out which orders of gods those deities came from. "

msgctxt "an8.64:7.2"
msgid "‘imā devatā amukamhā vā amukamhā vā devanikāyā’ti; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an8.64:7.3"
msgid "no ca kho tā devatā jānāmi: "
msgstr "But I didn’t know what "

msgctxt "an8.64:7.4"
msgid "‘imā devatā imassa kammassa vipākena ito cutā tattha upapannā’ti … pe … "
msgstr "deeds caused those deities to be reborn there after passing away from here. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.64:7.5"
msgid "tā ca devatā jānāmi: "
msgstr "So after some time … I found out what "

msgctxt "an8.64:7.6"
msgid "‘imā devatā imassa kammassa vipākena ito cutā tattha upapannā’ti; "
msgstr "deeds caused those deities to be reborn there after passing away from here. "

msgctxt "an8.64:7.7"
msgid "no ca kho tā devatā jānāmi: "
msgstr "But I didn’t know what "

msgctxt "an8.64:7.8"
msgid "‘imā devatā imassa kammassa vipākena evamāhārā evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvediniyo’ti … pe … "
msgstr "deeds caused those deities to have such food and such an experience of pleasure and pain. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.64:7.9"
msgid "tā ca devatā jānāmi: "
msgstr "So after some time … I found out what "

msgctxt "an8.64:7.10"
msgid "‘imā devatā imassa kammassa vipākena evamāhārā evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvediniyo’ti; "
msgstr "deeds caused those deities to have such food and such an experience of pleasure and pain. "

msgctxt "an8.64:7.11"
msgid "no ca kho tā devatā jānāmi: "
msgstr "But I didn’t know that "

# NOTE: There’s no witness in MS or PTS for imassa kammassa vipakena here, but BB includes it. It’s either an oversight, or he thinks it was unintentionally lost by abbreviation.
msgctxt "an8.64:7.12"
msgid "‘imā devatā evaṃdīghāyukā evaṃciraṭṭhitikā’ti … pe … "
msgstr "these deities have a life-span of such a length. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.64:7.13"
msgid "tā ca devatā jānāmi: "
msgstr "So after some time … I found out that "

msgctxt "an8.64:7.14"
msgid "‘imā devatā evaṃdīghāyukā evaṃciraṭṭhitikā’ti; "
msgstr "these deities have a life-span of such a length. "

msgctxt "an8.64:7.15"
msgid "no ca kho tā devatā jānāmi yadi vā me imāhi devatāhi saddhiṃ sannivutthapubbaṃ yadi vā na sannivutthapubbanti. (4–7.) "
msgstr "But I didn’t know whether or not I had previously lived together with those deities. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.304, sc8
msgctxt "an8.64:8.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me, "

msgctxt "an8.64:8.2"
msgid "‘sace kho ahaṃ obhāsañceva sañjāneyyaṃ, rūpāni ca passeyyaṃ, tāhi ca devatāhi saddhiṃ santiṭṭheyyaṃ sallapeyyaṃ sākacchaṃ samāpajjeyyaṃ, tā ca devatā jāneyyaṃ: "
msgstr "‘What if I were to perceive light and see visions; and associate with those deities, converse, and engage in discussion; "

msgctxt "an8.64:8.3"
msgid "“imā devatā amukamhā vā amukamhā vā devanikāyā”ti, tā ca devatā jāneyyaṃ: "
msgstr "and find out which orders of gods those deities come from; "

msgctxt "an8.64:8.4"
msgid "“imā devatā imassa kammassa vipākena ito cutā tattha upapannā”ti, tā ca devatā jāneyyaṃ: "
msgstr "and what deeds caused those deities to be reborn there after passing away from here; "

msgctxt "an8.64:8.5"
msgid "“imā devatā evamāhārā evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvediniyo”ti, tā ca devatā jāneyyaṃ: "
msgstr "and what deeds caused those deities to have such food and such an experience of pleasure and pain; "

msgctxt "an8.64:8.6"
msgid "“imā devatā evaṃdīghāyukā evaṃciraṭṭhitikā”ti, tā ca devatā jāneyyaṃ yadi vā me imāhi devatāhi saddhiṃ sannivutthapubbaṃ yadi vā na sannivutthapubbanti; "
msgstr "and that these deities have a life-span of such a length; and whether or not I have previously lived together with those deities. "

msgctxt "an8.64:8.7"
msgid "evaṃ me idaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ parisuddhataraṃ assā’ti. "
msgstr "Then my knowledge and vision would become even more purified.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "an8.64:9.1"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, aparena samayena appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto obhāsañceva sañjānāmi, rūpāni ca passāmi, tāhi ca devatāhi saddhiṃ santiṭṭhāmi sallapāmi sākacchaṃ samāpajjāmi, tā ca devatā jānāmi: "
msgstr "So after some time … "

msgctxt "an8.64:9.2"
msgid "‘imā devatā amukamhā vā amukamhā vā devanikāyā’ti, tā ca devatā jānāmi: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an8.64:9.3"
msgid "‘imā devatā imassa kammassa vipākena ito cutā tattha upapannā’ti, tā ca devatā jānāmi: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an8.64:9.4"
msgid "‘imā devatā evamāhārā evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvediniyo’ti, tā ca devatā jānāmi: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an8.64:9.5"
msgid "‘imā devatā evaṃdīghāyukā evaṃciraṭṭhitikā’ti, tā ca devatā jānāmi yadi vā me devatāhi saddhiṃ sannivutthapubbaṃ yadi vā na sannivutthapubbanti. (8) "
msgstr "I found out whether or not I have previously lived together with those deities. "

# NOTE: Note use of adhideva here.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.305, sc10
#. VAR: abhisambuddho’ti → abhisambuddho (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an8.64:10.1"
msgid "Yāvakīvañca me, bhikkhave, evaṃ aṭṭhaparivaṭṭaṃ adhidevañāṇadassanaṃ na suvisuddhaṃ ahosi, neva tāvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ‘sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambuddho’ti paccaññāsiṃ. "
msgstr "As long as my knowledge and vision about the deities was not fully purified from these eight perspectives, I didn’t announce my supreme perfect awakening in this world with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.64:10.2"
msgid "Yato ca kho me, bhikkhave, evaṃ aṭṭhaparivaṭṭaṃ adhidevañāṇadassanaṃ suvisuddhaṃ ahosi, athāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ‘sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambuddho’ti paccaññāsiṃ; "
msgstr "But when my knowledge and vision about the deities was fully purified from these eight perspectives, I announced my supreme perfect awakening in this world with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans. "

msgctxt "an8.64:10.3"
msgid "ñāṇañca pana me dassanaṃ udapādi; "
msgstr "Knowledge and vision arose in me: "

#. VAR: cetovimutti → vimutti (si, mr)
msgctxt "an8.64:10.4"
msgid "akuppā me cetovimutti; ayamantimā jāti natthi dāni punabbhavo”ti. "
msgstr "‘My freedom is unshakable; this is my last rebirth; now there are no more future lives.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an8.64:10.5"
msgid "Catutthaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
